annotationA: Cell division cycle 16 (Cdc16) is an essential subunit of the anaphase promoting complex/cyclosome (APC/C). Cdc16, together with other subunits, forms a functional subcomplex of the APC/C that binds to shtd and is likely to be involved in activator and substrate binding
annotationB: Anaphase-promoting complex subunit 10; Component of the anaphase promoting complex/cyclosome (APC/C), a cell cycle-regulated ubiquitin ligase that controls progression through mitosis and the G1 phase of the cell cycle
